OL,3,CWhat is FIFA's thunderstorm protocol
OL,4,Cand which World Cup games are at risk?
OL,6,FThe Hard Rock Stadium in Miami,
OL,7,FFlorida, will host seven World Cup
OL,8,Fmatches this summer, including
OL,9,FScotland's game against Brazil on June
OL,10,F24, a quarter-final, and the bronze
OL,11,Ffinal clash.
OL,13,FAtlanta, Boston, Dallas, Houston,
OL,14,FKansas City, and New Jersey are also
OL,15,Fsusceptible to thunderstorms, as are
OL,16,FMexico City and Monterrey in Mexico.
OL,18,FThe MetLife Stadium - which has been
OL,19,Fforced to change its name to the New
OL,20,FYork New Jersey Stadium - will host
OL,21,Fthe World Cup final on July 19.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
